node.text:
Not all interiors are staged scenes that exist behind closed doors only. This project by @aimarchitecture presents an integration of life, local character and street culture, blurring indoor and outdoor boundaries. Unlike the current tendency of centralising social life around The CBD, the PARK Mall is hidden within a bustling Jing’an city block, taking shape in a new kind of mini department store in Shanghai.⁠
⁠⁠
📸 @wen_studio2020⁠⁠

node.text:
Design by architect @solmaz_primavera_achitect (Solmaz Fooladi)
Materil_Microcement-metal-fiberglass
Item dimensions- W * D * H, cm 3800 * 1400 * 770h
The “drops of concrete” table is designed for 10-12 people. Made of fiberglass to make the structure lighter. Covered with microcement, which gives the illusion of solid cast concrete, one of the supports is made of metal reinforcement. The construction is rigid and light at the same time. There is also built-in electrical accessories.

node.text:
LUDWIG MIES VAN DER ROHE
1886-1969 → 2021

[CAT] Tal dia com avui de 1969, l'arquitecte Mies van der Rohe va morir a Chicago, Illinois. 52 anys després, continuem admirant la seva obra i promovent el coneixement del seu #llegat.
Més informació sobre la seva història a: www.miesbcn.com

[ENG] On a day like today in 1969, architect Mies van der Rohe died in Chicago, Illinois.
52 years later, we continue admiring his work and promoting the knowledge of his #legacy.
Find out more about his story at: www.miesbcn.com

[ESP] Tal día como hoy de 1969, el arquitecto Mies van der Rohe murió en Chicago, Illinois. 52 años después, seguimos admirando su obra y promoviendo el conocimiento de su #legado.
Más información e historia: www.miesbcn.com

🎥⬇️
Créditos de la edición: @baukunst_tv
Eugenia Soto (@esc_arq) e Iñaki Volante (@anewsublime).
Documental original 'MIES' de Michael Blackwood.
Derechos: @fundacion.arquia 

Via @fundaciomies
